title: [u'GIS', u'transportation', u'Central Ohio', u'MORPC', u'County', u'MPO', u'NonProfit', u'Regional Council', u'Regional Association', u'sidewalks', u'line', u'data', u'Geographic Information Systems', u'sidewalk']
modified: This sidewalk dataset is a comprehensive transportation network of over 221,000 features representing existing sidewalks, existing crosswalks (marked/unmarked), and sidewalk gaps and matches the cardinality of unique Location-Based Reference System (LBRS) road centerline databases for Franklin, Delaware, Fairfield, and Licking Counties in Ohio. All data was digitized in Esri ArcGIS 10.2.1 software in the Ohio South State Plane (NAD 83), feet projection. This sidewalk inventory is intended for planning purposes only. TranSystems does not warrant the accurateness of the sidewalks or crosswalks depicted in this dataset. None of the sidewalk or crosswalk segments have been field verified. Every reasonable effort has been made to reflect the correct GIS segmentation of all sidewalks, crosswalks, and sidewalk gaps. MORPC will facilitate the maintenance of this data by engaging local governments.
